This piece was written about the year 1600, before he had quitted theoClassics for the (Christian) FatherS.’ On entering upon his study of Divinity, Hall seems to have despised this sportive ebullition, and it is to , his friend William Knight, to whom he had entrusted the MS„ that we are indebted for its preservation and publication.
